                <head>300. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Executive Order 10945, “Administration of the Export Control Act of 1949,” was
                    signed by the President on May 24, 1961, establishing the Export Control Review
                    Board, a Cabinet committee consisting of the Secretaries of Commerce (Chairman),
                    State, and Defense. (Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June
                    12, 1961, pages 934-935; 26 <hi rend="italic">Federal</hi> Register 4487) Its
                    purpose was to assure high-level consideration of trade control policies and
                    actions and to obtain agreed action among Departments chiefly concerned with
                    advising the Secretary of Commerce, in accordance with the Export Control Act of
                    1949, as amended. (50 USC App. 2021, 2024)</p>
            </div>
